=================================================================================
===================  "reboot_test"  =============================================
=================================================================================

Check CPSS presence as PCIE-EndPoint after reboot
-------------------------------------------------
- reboot_test_run.sh-SONiC (described below)
- reboot_test_pcie.sh  - quick Debian-Only (no SONiC start), STOPs on error


=================  reboot_test_run.sh-SONiC  =============================================
When this "reboot_test" installed it does:
**************
Starts as SERVICE
Prints
    reboot_test no.NN started ---------------------------
 where NN is test-cycle counter
Waits 220 sec to apply "msai" and check the "msai" result
IF the result is OK, prints
   reboot_test no.NN passed
IF the result is "fail", prints and saves the /var/log/syslog in /host/reboot/test/slreboot.NN.flt
   reboot_test no.NN failed
Remove /etc/sonic/config_db.json on EVEN test-cyle (e.g. next ODD cycle starts without configuration),
but keep the config file for ODD cycle (e.g. next EVEN cycle goes with existing config file).
Always remove /var/log/syslog* to remove the history as preparation for next cycle
Go to reboot for next test-cycle
**************
Upon test failure (after the reboot) possible to see/get/report the SYSLOG files kept as
    /host/reboot/test/slreboot.NN.flt
    /host/reboot/test/slreboot.KK.flt

*********************************************************************
To INSTALL the test:
-------------------
cd /host/
scp ....../reboot_test.tar.gz
tar xf reboot_test.tar.gz
cd reboot_test
./reboot_test_install.sh
*********************************************************************
Start the test (after installation)
----------------------------------
reboot
*********************************************************************
Stop-Uninstall the test
-----------------------
/host/reboot_test/reboot_test_uninstall.sh


